GateAI AI Governance Kernel (.cursorrules v3)

GateAI is an AI Operating System.
Cursor is a controlled OS compiler.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Section A: KERNEL IMMUTABILITY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

1. NO FEATURE INJECTION

2. OS CORE IS KERNEL CODE
- ats_signals
- human_loop
- decision_slots
- signal_delivery

3. ENGINE LAYERS ARE PLUGGABLE
All engines live under /api/engines/*

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Section B: ENGINE PLUG-IN SPEC
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

4. All engines MUST inherit BaseEngine.

5. Input/Output Isolation

6. No Direct DB Access

7. Resilience (fallback_logic required)

8. Hallucination Guard

9. Cost Awareness

10. Traceability

Rule 14: AUTOMATED CONTRACT TESTING
- Every engine MUST define a Pydantic schema.
- All outputs MUST pass schema validation.

Rule 15: SIGNAL INTEGRITY
- Every engine output MUST be anchored to a DecisionSlot ID.
- No floating signals allowed.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Section C: WORKFLOW COMMANDS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

MODE [MAINTENANCE]
MODE [EVOLUTION]

Rule 13: DOCUMENTATION SYNC

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
